{"article_id":"BPYHeFMY36IF4xI4","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"WASHINGTON-Top administration officials forcefully defended the Iran nuclear deal Thursday before the Senate Foreign Relations Committee in the face of unified GOP opposition and some Democratic skepticism about the deal ' s capability","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"to deter a nuclear Iran .","depth":4},{"id":2,"text":"If Congress scuttles the deal","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"`` we will have squandered the best chance","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"we have","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"to solve this problem through peaceful means , ''","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"said Secretary of State John Kerry ,","depth":5},{"id":7,"text":"who appeared alongside Energy Secretary Ernest Moniz and Treasury Secretary Jack Lew .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"Thursday ' s hearing is the first public congressional forum","depth":4},{"id":9,"text":"to review terms of an agreement","depth":5},{"id":10,"text":"struck by the U.S. , Iran and five other nations","depth":6},{"id":11,"text":"and unanimously supported by the United Nations Security Council .","depth":6},{"id":12,"text":"Lawmakers are expected to vote on the deal this fall in what will be one of the most significant foreign policy votes","depth":5},{"id":13,"text":"to occur during the Obama presidency .","depth":5},{"id":14,"text":"Republicans in particular levied harsh critiques of the agreement","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to limit Iran 's nuclear ambitions in exchange for easing sanctions .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"\" With all due respect , you guys have been bamboozled ,","depth":10},{"id":17,"text":"and the American people are going to pay for that , ''","depth":10},{"id":18,"text":"said Sen. James Risch , R-Idaho .","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"Sen. Marco Rubio , R-Fla. , a 2016 presidential candidate","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"who has carved out a role as a foreign policy hawk ,","depth":10},{"id":21,"text":"had a testy exchange with Kerry .","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"`` I listened to a long list of your objections here about it ,","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"but there is no alternative","depth":14},{"id":24,"text":"that you or anybody else has proposed ''","depth":14},{"id":25,"text":"to stop a nuclear Iran ,","depth":13},{"id":26,"text":"Kerry said .","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"\" I sure have , Secretary Kerry , \"","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"Rubio responded .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"`` I am confident","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"that the next president of the United States will have enough common sense","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"that","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"if this is being applied properly ,","depth":15},{"id":33,"text":"if it is being implemented fully ,","depth":15},{"id":34,"text":"they ' re not going to arbitrarily end it , ''","depth":14},{"id":35,"text":"Kerry replied .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"Kerry said","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"any congressional effort","depth":10},{"id":38,"text":"to undermine the deal","depth":10},{"id":39,"text":"would send a message","depth":11},{"id":40,"text":"that America can ' t be trusted in international negotiations","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"after leading world powers all signed off on the deal .","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"The message would be :","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"\" We ' ve got 535 secretaries of State","depth":12},{"id":44,"text":"and you can ' t deal with anybody ,","depth":12},{"id":45,"text":"and that 's going to undo a whole bunch of efforts and a whole bunch of things","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"that matter in the world \"","depth":12},{"id":47,"text":"Kerry said .","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"Rubio also chastised the administration","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"for not doing more","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"to secure the release of American hostages ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"including Washington Post reporter Jason Rezaian ,","depth":11},{"id":52,"text":"who has been imprisoned for a year .","depth":11},{"id":53,"text":"Rezaian ' s brother attended Thursday ' s hearing .","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"The panel ' s chairman , Sen. Bob Corker , R-Tenn. , blasted `` hyperbole '' from the administration","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that `` it 's either this deal or war ''","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"and listed a number of weaknesses","depth":11},{"id":57,"text":"he sees in the agreement","depth":11},{"id":58,"text":"regarding the caliber of the inspections , the timeline","depth":12},{"id":59,"text":"to ease sanctions ,","depth":12},{"id":60,"text":"and Iran 's ability","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"to continue a nuclear program .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"`` I 'd have to say","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"that ,","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"based on my reading","depth":13},{"id":65,"text":"-- and I believe","depth":13},{"id":66,"text":"that you have crossed a new threshold in U.S. foreign policy --","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"where now it is a policy of the United States to enable a state sponsor of terror to obtain sophisticated , industrial nuclear development program","depth":14},{"id":68,"text":"that has ,","depth":16},{"id":69,"text":"as we know ,","depth":16},{"id":70,"text":"only one real practical need , ''","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"Corker said .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"Even the panel 's top Democrats , Sen. Ben Cardin , D-Md. , and Bob Menendez , D-N.J. , appeared skeptical about the deal ,","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"and neither has indicated","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"they can support it yet .","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"Congress has until Sept. 17 to vote","depth":4},{"id":76,"text":"to approve , disapprove or take no action at all .","depth":4},{"id":77,"text":"Obama has said","depth":4},{"id":78,"text":"he would veto any bill","depth":5},{"id":79,"text":"to block it .","depth":5},{"id":80,"text":"With Republicans in control of Congress","depth":5},{"id":81,"text":"and party leaders","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"working to kill the deal ,","depth":6},{"id":83,"text":"the administration 's strategy appears to be to shore up enough Democratic support","depth":5},{"id":84,"text":"to block a veto override ,","depth":6},{"id":85,"text":"which would require the support of at least 34 senators or 146 House members .","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"To that end , the trio of administration officials met privately Thursday afternoon with House Democrats .","depth":4},{"id":87,"text":"Minority Leader Nancy Pelosi , D-Calif. , is helping the administration shore up the support","depth":6},{"id":88,"text":"President Obama needs .","depth":6},{"id":89,"text":"`` I feel very confident","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"we 're going to have enough votes ''","depth":8},{"id":91,"text":"to block a veto override ,","depth":8},{"id":92,"text":"said Rep. Jan Schakowsky , D-Ill. ,","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"who supports the agreement ,","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"following the meeting .","depth":7}],"relations":[{"parent":189,"left":169,"right":188,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":169,"left":102,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":102,"left":96,"right":101,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":96,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":101,"left":99,"right":100,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":99,"left":2,"right":98,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":98,"left":97,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":97,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":100,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":168,"left":105,"right":167,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":105,"left":8,"right":104,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":104,"left":9,"right":103,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":103,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":167,"left":106,"right":166,"relation":